text.tspan: Death rate from unsafe water vs. GDP per capita, 2019
Death rates are measured as the number of deaths per 100,000 individuals. GDP per capita is measured in constant
international-$, which corrects for inflation and price differences between countries.
Source: IHME, Global Burden of Disease (2019); Data compiled from multiple sources by World Bank
